FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779887471
OL,3,CNASA unveils plans for permanent moon
OL,4,Cbase as stepping stone to Mars
OL,6,FThe space agency plans to establish a
OL,7,Fcamp near the lunar south pole, "one
OL,8,Fof the most strategically and
OL,9,Fscientifically valuable regions on the
OL,10,Fmoon," which will support humans
OL,11,Fliving and working there.
OL,13,FThe ambitious project will eventually
OL,14,Fstretch hundreds of square miles
OL,15,Facross the lunar south pole region, an
OL,16,Farea of the moon whose environmental
OL,17,Fconditions make it well-suited for
OL,18,Fhuman exploration.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779887471
OL,3,CNASA unveils plans for permanent moon
OL,4,Cbase as stepping stone to Mars
OL,6,FUnlike many regions of the moon that
OL,7,Fexperience long periods of darkness
OL,8,Ffollowed by long periods of daylight,
OL,9,Fparts of the South Pole receive
OL,10,Fextended sunlight and shorter periods
OL,11,Fof shadow, NASA said.
OL,13,FAs well as the opportunities that will
OL,14,Fcome with building a permanent base on
OL,15,Fthe moon, the outpost will be a
OL,16,Fstepping stone to NASA's next goal:
OL,17,Fgetting to Mars.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
